  "texts": [
    "Line scanning, or pushbroom, is especially popular in food inspection due to its consistency and efficiency in on-line applications.",
    "A typical pushbroom HSI system includes a CCD (Charge-Coupled Device) or CMOS (Complementary Metal Oxide Semiconductor) camera, an illumination unit, a spectrograph with a C-mount lens, and computer software for image acquisition (Kim et al. 2022).",
    "Although HSI captures significantly more data than a standard RGB image and thus requires longer acquisition times, its detailed spectral data makes it invaluable for product quality analysis.",
    "Consequently, HSI technology has become a valuable tool in the agri-food domain.",
    "With increased expectations for high-quality and safe agri-food products, the need for accurate, fast, and objective quality determination of these characteristics continues to grow."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "A typical pushbroom HSI system includes a CCD (Charge-Coupled Device) or CMOS (Complementary Metal Oxide Semiconductor) camera, an illumination unit, a spectrograph with a C-mount lens, and computer software for image acquisition (Kim et al. 2022)."
